---
title: Cauliflower and Brie Gratin with Clementine-Cucumber Salad
description: Gratin for dinner is always a great idea! Gratin—a dish of French origin that features layered vegetables topped with broiled breadcrumbs or cheese—is the ultimate veggie-forward meal. Our version highlights leeks, cauliflower and gooey brie cheese for a rustic and indulgent meal.

Ingredients: Cauliflower • Brie cheese (milk, salt, bacterial culture, microbial enzyme, mould culture) (milk) • Clementine • Cucumber • White cooking wine (cooking wine (wine, salt, potassium sorbate, malic acid, sulphites)) (sulphites) • Spring mix (lolla rosa multi-leaf lettuce, red flash red oak lettuce, red leaf multi-leaf lettuce, green oak lettuce, bally hoo tango lettuce) • Leek • 35% Cream (cream, milk, dextrose, cellulose gel, carrageenan, mono and diglycerides, cellulose gum, polysorbate 80, sodium citrate, disodium phosphate) (milk) • Panko breadcrumbs (bleached wheat flour, yeast, sugar, salt) (wheat) • Cream sauce spice blend (wheat flour, salt, garlic powder, onion powder, canola oil, silicon dioxide) (wheat) • Honey • White wine vinegar (wine vinegar, potassium metabisulfite) (sulphites).
